How to minimize warping

‚úî Clamp/weight the PCB flat during heating
Use a metal block, plate, or flat thick aluminum heat spreader underneath.

‚úî Heat gradually rather than blasting one spot
Start with lower airflow or preheat the area.

‚úî Preheat the board (optional)
If you have a preheater or hot plate, preheat to ~120‚Äì150 ¬∞C first, then use hot air. This reduces temperature gradients dramatically.

‚úî Avoid heating large areas at once
Only heat the part you're soldering.

